South Africa Stocks Fall for Third Day; Anglo, Grindrod, Liberty, Massmart

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-24T12:41:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/south-africa-stocks-fall-for-third-day-anglo-grindrod-liberty-massmart.html
  South Africa ’s FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index weakened for a third day, falling 349.7, or 1.1
percent, to 31,582.37 as of 2:26 p.m. in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.    Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ), the diversified mining company
that makes up 11 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock
index, retreated to the lowest since Feb. 1, declining 4.41
rand, or 1.2 percent, to 358.66 rand. Copper fell for a fourth
day on concern that tension in the Middle East and Africa,
including the revolt in Libya, may hamper global growth.    Grindrod Ltd . (GND SJ), Africa’s biggest shipping company,
dropped lost 93 cents, or 6.1 percent, to 14.37 rand, the lowest
since July 8. Grindrod said profit fell 11 percent to 780.3
million rand ($109 million) in the year through December.    Liberty Holdings Ltd . (LBH SJ), the insurer controlled by
Africa’s largest bank, slipped for a third day, losing 90 cents,
or 1.2 percent, to 74.50 rand. The company reported 2010 new
business contracted by 1.9 percent, reducing the profit it makes
from sales, according to a statement.    Massmart Holdings Ltd . (MSM SJ), the retailer selling a
controlling stake to Wal-Mart Stores Inc., slumped for a third
day, losing 3.08 rand, or 2.1 percent, to 141.91 rand. The
company said its fiscal full-year operating profit will grow at
a slower pace during the rest of the year than during the first
half through December.    Stefanutti Stocks Holdings Ltd . (SSK SJ), the South African
construction and engineering company, declined 30 cents, or 2.7
percent, to 11 rand, the lowest since Feb. 7. Stefanutti said it
was in undisclosed discussions which may affect the price of its
securities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
